    {
      "title": "Correlation Trace API Endpoints",
      "type": "text",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 29 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## Per-Request Trace Queries\n\nPrometheus stores aggregate metrics. For per-request trace data, use the Admin Ops API with a correlation ID.\n\n### Receipts for a correlation ID\n```\nGET /admin/ops/receipts?correlation_id=<UUID>\nHeader: X-Admin-Token: <jwt>\n```\n\n### Provider calls for a correlation ID\n```\nGET /admin/ops/provider-calls?correlation_id=<UUID>\nHeader: X-Admin-Token: <jwt>\n```\n\n### Incidents linked to a correlation ID\n```\nGET /admin/ops/incidents?trace_id=<UUID>\nHeader: X-Admin-Token: <jwt>\n```\n\n### Deep Health Check\n```\nGET /admin/ops/health/deep\n```\nReturns cascading dependency status: Postgres, Redis, OpenAI, n8n.\n\n---\n\n**Tip:** The X-Correlation-Id header is set on every response. Capture it from the client to trace end-to-end."
      }
    }
